<div id="review_1066581303" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1066581303" />
    <a title="Jean Riescher" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/20969379-jean-riescher"><img alt="Jean Riescher" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1370261683p2/20969379.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1066581303?book_show_action=true">Sep 28, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jean Riescher" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jean Riescher" href="/user/show/20969379-jean-riescher">Jean Riescher</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1066581303" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4752331880968418030">What do you search for in a book? Character, insight, beauty, pain and something that lives on beyond the page. These vignettes, each describing different moments in a therapeutic relationship with varied patients give hope, comfort, insight and also frustrate, agitate and discomfort the reader through the same from Dr. Yalom. <br/><br/>This is a book that lives--even as it struggles with death. Truly a gift.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

