<div id="review_3284607736" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3284607736" />
    <a title="Maryam Samiei" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/25859356-maryam-samiei"><img alt="Maryam Samiei" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1625490241p2/25859356.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3284607736?book_show_action=true">Apr 19, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Maryam Samiei" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Maryam Samiei" href="/user/show/25859356-maryam-samiei">Maryam Samiei</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3284607736" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1613541017885052937"><br/>This book consists of ten true stories, interwoven with psychological insights and helpful solutions. Since I saw my feelings mirrored throughout the book, I could hardly hold myself away from each and every story. They all had great impact on my perspective. Their main themes, if I can put it this way, were death anxiety and how to have a meaningful life.<br/><br/>What came to my mind while reading was how Yalom, at that time having more than 80 years of age, was critical of himself while approaching eac</span>
  <span id="freeText1613541017885052937" style="display:none"><br />This book consists of ten true stories, interwoven with psychological insights and helpful solutions. Since I saw my feelings mirrored throughout the book, I could hardly hold myself away from each and every story. They all had great impact on my perspective. Their main themes, if I can put it this way, were death anxiety and how to have a meaningful life.<br /><br />What came to my mind while reading was how Yalom, at that time having more than 80 years of age, was critical of himself while approaching each client. He prevented common solutions since he believed they are all unique. And this uniqueness meant that common psychological disorders and classifications are no longer valid since this may lead to unsatisfactory and vague conclusions.<br /><br />I read the stories as if I was sipping my strong coffee, dreadfully anticipating its end :) <br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="1613541017885052937" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


