  <span id="freeText15346641718807853916" style="display:none">I loved reading this because it is the case studies of a renowned psychiatrist, Dr. Yalom, who can write about his patients with a clear and interesting manner that makes you want to know more. You feel as if you are right there in the therapist's office and listening and watching as the six patients tell their stories and work through their issues. It is compelling, inviting and engaging. As a frustrated therapist wannabe it was just a perfect read! I recommend it, especially if you always wanted to be a fly on the wall after the door was closed in the therapist's office, leaving you alone in the waiting room. </span>
