    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1639667923" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1639667923" />
    <a title="Katey Briana" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5221918-katey-briana"><img alt="Katey Briana" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1612490661p2/5221918.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1639667923?book_show_action=true">May 16, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Katey Briana" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Katey Briana" href="/user/show/5221918-katey-briana">Katey Briana</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1639667923" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer691997824882126197">I will preface this review with the fact I am not the biggest fan of existentialism. Having said that, after the first chapter I was in love. Yalom is a masterful storyteller, sharing the therapeutic journey with each of his clients. Understanding this, it is difficult to differentiate fact from fiction, as was Yalom&apos;s intent. As a therapist, I would have preferred to know more about the original sessions instead of the fanciful afterthoughts. </span>
  <span id="freeText691997824882126197" style="display:none">I will preface this review with the fact I am not the biggest fan of existentialism. Having said that, after the first chapter I was in love. Yalom is a masterful storyteller, sharing the therapeutic journey with each of his clients. Understanding this, it is difficult to differentiate fact from fiction, as was Yalom's intent. As a therapist, I would have preferred to know more about the original sessions instead of the fanciful afterthoughts. </span>
  <a data-text-id="691997824882126197" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

