    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2067473575" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2067473575" />
    <a title="Suha" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/33599214-suha"><img alt="Suha" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1407013913p2/33599214.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2067473575?book_show_action=true">Aug 06, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Suha" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Suha" href="/user/show/33599214-suha">Suha</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780349407425" href="/book/show/25996867-creatures-of-a-day-and-other-tales-of-psychotherapy">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2067473575" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9576068341573950097">Yalom’s “Creatures of a Day” is a non-fiction book representing 10 short stories / cases about his clients who were facing death and revealing the hidden behaviors of his clients from the fear of the end of their lives. What is interesting is that Yalom, is old himself and he had to face this fear together with his clients “I am old, quite old, and I have thought about my death. But still I&apos;m a bit rattled by your comment. … I think it&apos;s because I just don&apos;t want to be defined as an old person.&quot;</span>
  <span id="freeText9576068341573950097" style="display:none">Yalom’s “Creatures of a Day” is a non-fiction book representing 10 short stories / cases about his clients who were facing death and revealing the hidden behaviors of his clients from the fear of the end of their lives. What is interesting is that Yalom, is old himself and he had to face this fear together with his clients “I am old, quite old, and I have thought about my death. But still I'm a bit rattled by your comment. … I think it's because I just don't want to be defined as an old person." <br />In this book you get to peek at what exists behind the doors of psychotherapists and their clients as we all wonder about the process of healing, is it a word? Is it a school of thought? Is it coincidence? I got to experience the fear of death and the fear of Yalom as a therapist not being able to ease his clients’ pains and fears. <br />In each chapter, we meet a client and we see both Yalom and his client vulnerable attempting to find a way of peace of mind and contentment in one’s remaining days of life. <br />On a personal note, being young myself, reading this book allowed me to live the near death psyche and understand what life might look like in a moment like that, whether because I am going to get old one day, or face a disease. Death is coming to all of us and there is no hiding. <br />This book is well written, simple and insightful. Not of his best books, I certainly love his novels better.<br /><br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="9576068341573950097" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


